title: For Sale:  Browning Citori 725 Sporting 32" 12 GA
postcontent:
Only about a box of shells through it! Immaculate condition comes with the extra chokes and the soft case. Hate to sell her, but I have not been able to shoot as much as I would like. Looking for $2250.00 cash and a face to face transaction if at all possible, but I would be willing to ship from an FFL to your FFL if you cover any fees and shipping. No trades please. REDACTED More pictures available upon request.

The new Citori 725 is the evolution of John M. Browning’s legendary B25 Superposed, now with the modern performance advantage of a Low-Profile receiver. The new 725 receiver is significantly lower than other Citori 12 gauge receivers, yet the 725 shares the renowned durability of generations of Citori over and unders with the same rugged full-width hinge pin and tapered locking bolt design.

With a 725, you get the "one with the gun" feeling you want, with the long lasting durability you expect from a Browning over and under. And the features don't stop there. The 725 showcases an all-new Mechanical Trigger (FireLite) that offers unmatched feel and lighter pull weights than ever before. Inflex Technology has also been added to make shooting more comfortable. Experience the benefits these improvements can do for your shooting with a new Citori 725.

Unique to the 725 Sporting Model
Signature 725 rounded fore arm with subtle palm rest is both comfortable and stylish
Barrel porting assists the shooter by reducing muzzle jump, enabling consistent sight plain and quick follow up shots.
HiViz Pro-Comp fiber-optic front sight and ivory mid-bead sight for excellent target acquisition even in low-light conditions.
Five Invector-DS extend choke tubes (Full, Improved Modified, Modified, Improved Cylinder, Skeet)
Beautiful gloss oil finish Grade III/IV Walnut
Gold accented Engraving

Receiver
The Low-Profile steel receiver of the Citori 725 is a triumph of modern design without sacrificing traditional strength, keeping the full-hinge pin and tapered locking bolt design that makes a Citori superior to weaker trunnion designs.
The silver nitride finish on the receiver is as tough as it is beautiful.

Barrel
Ventilated top rib provides a horizontal sighting plane, reduced heat mirage, and a classic sporting look.
Ventilated side rib reduces overall weight and aids in barrel cooling.
Vector Pro lengthened forcing cones provide improved shot patterns and superior durability, even with steel shot.
Invector-DS choke tubes are longer than traditional chokes, allowing for a consistent barrel taper at the muzzle. The double seal keeps fouling gasses out of the threads between the choke tube and the barrel.

Action
The Fire Lite Mechanical Trigger system design features reduced take up, a crip break, and shorter overtravel, resulting in a high performance trigger that doesn't require intertia to reset.
Hammer ejectors quickly and reliably clear the chambers for quick reloading.
Top-tang barrel selector/safety allow you to verify the status of the gun without unshouldering it.

Stock
Close radius pistol grip and palm swell with detailed checkering and classic lines for beauty without sacrificing function.
Inflex II recoil pad absorbs and deflects recoil away from the shooter's cheek, allowing you to shoot comfortably for longer periods of time.



THE BEST TARGET SHOTGUN EVER BUILT. Unlike other Low-Profile guns that rely on undersized trunnions and narrow, tapered pins to lock up their receivers, the 725 still has the rugged full-width hinge pin and transverse mounted locking bolt design of the original Citori. That means the 725 Sporting is built strong enough to compete year after year and round after round of breaking clay targets. While this kind of use will wear out lesser Low-Profile over and unders, it simply wears a Citori in.

If that isn't enough, the new Fire Lite Mechanical Trigger delivers a smooth pull with a lighter squeeze than other Citori sporting guns. Inflex Technology recoil control keeps you shooting all day with none of the beat down feeling you can get with lesser recoil pads. Not to mention the totally redesigned Invector DS choke system gives more consistent patterns with more predictable scaling of chock constrictions than ever before. title: For Sale/Trade:  1965 Mustang
postcontent:
Want to sell or TRADE for a 16-20' Bay/Center console type boat with motor and trailer of EQUAL value.

New Orleans, La.

Car runs and has a clean title. It is about 80% restored I guess. Motor has $4000 in it alone.

500 miles since rebuild.

Motor: bored 30/10 with Edlebrock carb, intake, valve springs, cam, timing chain/gears. Crane Cam roller rockers and hardened push rods. Summit racing pistons/rings. New oil pump and fuel pump. Converted the alternator to a one wire set up and an HEI distributor to get rid of points system. Clutched cooling fan from a 1991 Mercury Grand Marquis. (The original stiff bladed fan made an insane amount of noise.)

Exhaust: Thrust glass packs with side dump just in front of the rear tires. Sound great with a low rumble but too loud.

Brand new aluminum racing radiator.

Trans: T-5 from a 1994 Mustang Cobra, new clutch plate, hydraulic clutch, trans completely rebuilt at same time as motor. New drive shaft. Rebuilt 8' rear from a 1966 Mustang, replaced 2.79:1 gears with 3.50:1 gears with new trans. 

All new suspension. Replaced exterior lighting with HiD and LED.

Steering: Unisteer manual rack and pinion ($1000). Complete 'Granada Swap' on front spindles. I used the front spindles from a 1977 Granada for the disc brakes and a larger braking surface. Replaced the single cylinder (Suicide cylinder) master brake cylinder with a new 1974 Maverick master cylinder. New brakes all the way around.

Interior is in awesome shape. I currently have 2006 Mustang GT seats installed for the high back and head rest that the original seats did not have. I installed torque boxes and sub-frame connectors. Replaced the front floor boards and sanded then painted the interior and underneath with bed liner.

I have the original seats in my garage under a cover. I also have like 3 boxes of parts to go with the car as well as almost all the receipts and work I did to the car. 

What still needs to be addressed with the car: 

Minor body work. There is very little rust on the car. It has been garage kept since I bought it 5 years ago.

There is a 'clunking' noise from the left rear of the car, I think this could be the left rear axle. This just started happening and I haven't been able to look into it. Steering is still a bit stiff since there is less than 500 miles on the car since I installed the new rack and pinion.

The reason I am selling is that I had surgery to rebuild my left elbow and left wrist so can't really turn wrenches as well anymore. Also, I am retiring 01 Sep 15 and do not have the money to finish the car like it should be.

This is my photobucket album for the car. Let me know if you can get in to it.

title: For Sale:  Glock model 22 .40 S&W, Semi Custom, plus extras
postcontent:
I’m selling my Gen 2 Glock model 22 that has very few original Glock parts left on it. I built this pistol from a police trade in (Maryland State Police, if memory serves) gen 2.

I built it with steel challenge matches in mind, but it’ll work well for most any type of pistol competition (USPA, IPDA, etc). I decided to change to 1911 in 9MM so the Glock I just sitting around going to waste, total round count on the pistol since reworked – about 600.

Mods include: 
Lone Wolf match grade barrel 
Lone Wolf “Pro Pick” trigger kit (3 ½# disconnector, mid weight striker spring, 6lb trigger spring, ultimate trigger stop) 
2 Lightning strike captured springs on full length S/S guide rods (17# for full power loads, 13# for 750 fps soft loads) 
Dawson fiber optic front and rear sights 
Extended slide release and take down levers 
Hard chrome plated slide by Rock Your Glock
A Grip grip enhancer sleave
Those with a keen eye will notice the finger grooves on the front of the frame that the gen 2s didn’t have. What I did was cut the finger grooves off a Hogue grip sleeve and glue them onto the front of the frame, under the A Grip wrap. I used a small amount of silicone glue, so if you don’t like the feel they can easily be peeled off.

Also included in the deal:
4 15 rnd mags (2 new, 2 well used but still serviceable)
2 kydex holsters
Laser snap cap
Soft case
All parts to return pistol to OEM
I’d prefer to meet face to face, but will ship, and only through an FFL, if your FFL does not accept firearms from individuals, you pay the FFL fee on my end.

title: For Sale:  Springfield Armory SOCOM 16 M1A .308 Winchester 7.62 x 51 NATO Semi Auto Rifle
postcontent:
Guns For Sale - Springfield Armory SOCOM 16 -- M1A .308 Winchester 7.62 x 51 NATO Semi Auto Rifle

LSB#: 121227TA07

Make: Springfield Armory

Model: M1A

Serial Number: 246218

Year of Manufacture:

Caliber: 7.62 x 51 NATO, .308 Winchester

Action Type: Semi-Automatic with detachable magazine.

Markings: The receiver is marked “U.S. RIFLE M1A / SPRINGFIELD / ARMORY / 246218” The front sight is marked “Trijicon”. The bolt and roller assembly is marked “7790186- SA / F00205”. The charging handle is marked “SOCOM 16” and “7267064-2 / SA”. The magazine has the Springfield crossed cannons logo on it.

Barrel Length: The barrel is approximately 16.25” and 17 7/8” to the end of the break. The barrel has 6 Grooves with a 1:11 Right Hand Twist.

Sights / Optics: The front sight is a Trijicon XS sights post with Tritium insert. The rear sight is an enlarged military aperture (Ghost Ring), adjustable for windage and elevation. This rifle also comes equipped with a forward-mounted scope base that is ideal for electronic sights or other accessories.

Stock Configuration & Condition: The stock is a light weight one piece black Synthetic stock. This stock only has very light handling marks. The LOP measures approximately 13 ¼” from the front of the trigger to the back of the metal USGI buttplate. The stock rates in about Excellent overall condition.

Type of Finish: Matte

Finish Originality: Factory Original

Bore Condition: The bore is Bright and the rifling is Sharp. There is no apparent erosion. This rifle appears to have never been fired

Overall Condition: This rifle retains about 99% of its metal finish. The balance of the finish shows very light handling marks. The screw heads are Sharp. The markings are Clear. Overall, this rifle rates in about Excellent condition.

Mechanics: The action functions correctly. We have not fired this rifle.

Box, Paperwork & Accessories: Included with this rifle is the technical manual for M1A type riffles, Springfield Armory Instruction manual, and a nice article that was included with the rifle when purchased about the “Mysterious Slam Fire”.

Our Assessment: This 16” version of the M1A can be an effective close quarters battle rifle or just a great “ranch gun”. It has a proprietary muzzle brake, tritium front sight and a forward-mounted scope base ready to mount your optics and accessories. The nice compact size of this high powered rifle is something not to be messed with. Pigs will run in fear when they hear your truck.
